  "texts": [
    "Table 2 displays the notable establishments involved in international research on the digital transformation of small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs).",
    "The modularity value, also known as the Q value, is a metric used to assess the quality of community partitioning in a network graph.",
    "Typically, a Q value greater than 0.3 indicates a significant community structure regarding this network graph.",
    "The Q value is 0.8646, which signifies the clustering results' reliability and effectiveness.",
    "The University of Huddersfield, Grenoble Alpes University, the French National Center for Scientific Research, and the University of Ljubljana are prominent institutions known for their high publication frequencies."
